![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ea536a24-92db-48fb-95b1-cd9aac89a3c2/235.jpg)

It's the moment you have all been waiting for. The Dark Knight tops many peoples list when it comes to the greatest superhero films of all time, and for good reason. Its intense pacing, intriguing plot, and eccentric cast of characters have allowed this film to reach legendary status, but does it hold up after all this time? Join us as we continue our stroll down Memory Lane (or Crime Alley) and look back at all things The Dark Knight. From its homages to The Long Halloween, to debunking urban legends, this review is one for the ages! Grab your war paint, hockey pads, some gasoline and dynamite, and check out this review of The Dark Knight!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
